outpost
[TITLE]The Manual:  Your First Outpost[/TITLE]
When you start, your dwarves will be located near a cliff face with whatever animals and objects you decided to bring along.  If you've brought along somebody that knows how to fish or hunt, that dwarf will get to work, but the others will mill around, awaiting your orders.
[B]
Your ultimate goal is to extract every last ounce of wealth from the mountain, but first you need to survive the winter, so you need to get your dwarves to handle the basics.  Most orders are issued to your dwarves from buildings you've created, and others are issued by designating work areas.
[B]
The list of options can be daunting at first (and will remain daunting for a while).  Read the following sections to get a handle on individual aspects of running a simple fortress.
